Physique quantique et Categories
================================

https://golem.ph.utexas.edu/category/2007/03/a_topos_foundation_for_theorie.html
A Topos Foundation for Theories of Physics, Posted by John Baez

https://arxiv.org/abs/math/0004133
From Finite Sets to Feynman Diagrams [categorification and groupoids]
John C. Baez, James Dolan

MATHEMATICAL IDEAS AND NOTIONS OF QUANTUM FIELD THEORY
-> http://www-math.mit.edu/~etingof/lect.ps
Has a nice section on the euler characteristic of moduli spaces of curves,
and a proof that the Euler characteristic of the moduli space of elliptic
curves is -1/12; also available here: https://ncatlab.org/nlab/files/EulerCharacteristicOfSpaceOfCurves.pdf

https://webusers.imj-prg.fr/~frederic.paugam/documents/enseignement/master-mathematical-physics.pdf
Towards the mathematics of quantum field theory (An advanced course)
[utilise la higher category, doctrines, catégories monoïdales, 500 pages]

https://ncatlab.org/schreiber/show/Mathematical+Foundations+of+Quantum+Field+and+Perturbative+String+Theory
Hisham Sati, Urs Schreiber (eds.) [350 pages]
Mathematical Foundations of Quantum Field and Perturbative String Theory

https://ncatlab.org/schreiber/files/dcct170811.pdf
Differential cohomology in a cohesive ∞-topos
Urs Schreiber [1000 pages]

